# Allowlist: central core files with known provider/OS coupling and bash shebangs.
#
# Format:
#   <path>:<reason>
#
# Reason prefixes determine which check accepts the entry:
#   provider/OS reference - ...  — accepted by the provider/OS ID check
#   bash shebang - ...           — accepted by the bash language policy check
#
# Every provider/OS entry below is tracked Phase 3 extraction debt: the literal
# exists in core today and will move into the owning provider/plugin during
# Phase 3. No silent passes — if the scan finds a literal not listed here, the
# boundary check fails.

# --- Provider/OS coupling (Phase 3 extraction debt) ---
# These files reference the Docker CLI tool / Docker installation, not the
# "docker" provider ID. The substring match is a false positive (docker the
# tool name coincides with docker the provider id, added in v4.1 WS5).
eve_sdk/profile_resolve.py:provider/OS reference - Vagrant emit installs Docker as a package (not the docker provider)
scripts/doctor:provider/OS reference - ENGINE_TOOLS + docker_report reference the Docker CLI daemon check
scripts/eve-local-install:provider/OS reference - example step bundle mentions docker.sh
scripts/update-tools:provider/OS reference - updates the Docker CLI tool on the host

# --- Bash shebangs (language policy: no new bash in scripts/) ---
# (empty — all test runners ported to Python)
